00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:17.360 align:middle line:84%
What is integrative medicine,
and why that word integrative?

00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:19.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Integrative medicine,
as it's currently defined

00:05:19.460 --> 00:05:22.910 align:middle line:84%
and understood, developed
from what used to be called

00:05:22.910 --> 00:05:25.610 align:middle line:84%
complementary and
alternative medicine.

00:05:25.610 --> 00:05:28.430 align:middle line:84%
And that developed from what was
originally called whole person

00:05:28.430 --> 00:05:29.900 align:middle line:84%
medicine, which
was a movement here

00:05:29.900 --> 00:05:33.830 align:middle line:84%
in the west that also launched
in about the late '70s.

00:05:33.830 --> 00:05:36.890 align:middle line:84%
And whole person medicine
was inspired primarily

00:05:36.890 --> 00:05:40.940 align:middle line:84%
from a lot of the eastern
traditional whole person

00:05:40.940 --> 00:05:43.970 align:middle line:84%
medical systems, Ayurveda,
Tibetan medicine,

00:05:43.970 --> 00:05:47.480 align:middle line:84%
Chinese medicine, Native
American medicine.

00:05:47.480 --> 00:05:50.720 align:middle line:84%
All those traditions had an
understanding and a knowledge

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:54.120 align:middle line:84%
of really what the human being
is beyond the body, mind,

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:55.610 align:middle line:90%
and spirit.

00:05:55.610 --> 00:05:58.520 align:middle line:84%
And so currently
integrative medicine

00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:03.260 align:middle line:84%
is the practice of complementary
therapies such as acupuncture,

00:06:03.260 --> 00:06:07.580 align:middle line:84%
massage, osteopathic medicine,
energy medicine, such as Reiki

00:06:07.580 --> 00:06:10.820 align:middle line:84%
and healing touch, within
what's called the allopathic

00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:12.230 align:middle line:90%
or the biomedical model.

00:06:12.230 --> 00:06:14.940 align:middle line:84%
So at UCSD, for example,
where I am full time,

00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:17.300 align:middle line:84%
we have a center for
integrative medicine,

00:06:17.300 --> 00:06:20.480 align:middle line:84%
and it's throughout our
inpatient and hospital system.

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:23.180 align:middle line:84%
And people can get not only
their traditional therapies

00:06:23.180 --> 00:06:25.790 align:middle line:84%
and surgeries, but
they can be prescribed

00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:29.420 align:middle line:84%
acupuncture and energy
medicine and on and on and on.

00:06:29.420 --> 00:06:33.980 align:middle line:84%
It's very good, it's developed,
and it's made a big difference.

00:06:33.980 --> 00:06:36.330 align:middle line:84%
But there's more to
go, is my opinion.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:37.130 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sure.

00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:40.880 align:middle line:84%
It seems like it's a
fairly new approach

00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:44.960 align:middle line:84%
to take the old as well as
a lot of the new medicine

00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:48.230 align:middle line:84%
that we've, in the allopathic
model, been understanding.

00:06:48.230 --> 00:06:50.570 align:middle line:84%
So with that, what
would your definition

00:06:50.570 --> 00:06:53.090 align:middle line:90%
of integrative health then be?

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:54.890 align:middle line:84%
>> So integrative
health, I would say,

00:06:54.890 --> 00:06:58.970 align:middle line:84%
is the next iteration
beyond integrative medicine.

00:06:58.970 --> 00:07:01.670 align:middle line:84%
So integrative health is
as a term that's come,

00:07:01.670 --> 00:07:03.740 align:middle line:90%
maybe, the last few years.

00:07:03.740 --> 00:07:05.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's getting
more into the concept

00:07:05.690 --> 00:07:07.670 align:middle line:90%
of wellness and well-being.

00:07:07.670 --> 00:07:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And it is incorporating
more completely concepts

00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:14.120 align:middle line:84%
of spiritual well-being that
the integrative medicine

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:17.000 align:middle line:90%
model has yet to fully grasp.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:21.680 align:middle line:84%
And it's also doing a better
job appreciating and bringing

00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:25.430 align:middle line:84%
the whole person into
the medical system.

00:07:25.430 --> 00:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
But integrative health also
incorporates social health,

00:07:28.310 --> 00:07:30.170 align:middle line:90%
environmental health.

00:07:30.170 --> 00:07:32.620 align:middle line:84%
And this really circles back
to these traditional health

00:07:32.620 --> 00:07:36.980 align:middle line:84%
systems, which also took
all that into account when

00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:39.320 align:middle line:84%
they were trying to get
a human being to be well

00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:44.150 align:middle line:84%
again and healthy, and live a
whole life, a productive life.

00:07:44.150 --> 00:07:47.080 align:middle line:84%
>> So the current biomedical
paradigm right now,

00:07:47.080 --> 00:07:50.910 align:middle line:84%
how would you foresee
integrative medicine,

00:07:50.910 --> 00:07:52.850 align:middle line:84%
integrative health
fitting into that?

00:07:52.850 --> 00:07:54.380 align:middle line:90%
Is there resistance to it?

00:07:54.380 --> 00:07:57.540 align:middle line:84%
Or is it kind of an open
playing field right now?

00:07:57.540 --> 00:07:58.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Both.

00:07:58.670 --> 00:08:00.330 align:middle line:84%
Historically there
was resistance.

00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:02.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's why
integrative medicine--

00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:06.170 align:middle line:84%
the modalities such as
meditation and acupuncture that

00:08:06.170 --> 00:08:08.900 align:middle line:84%
are within the
biomedical model--

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:10.460 align:middle line:84%
they're so-called
evidence-based.

00:08:10.460 --> 00:08:12.980 align:middle line:84%
That means there's
been enough research

00:08:12.980 --> 00:08:16.490 align:middle line:84%
to show that they work, and
therefore we've allowed them

00:08:16.490 --> 00:08:18.557 align:middle line:90%
into the biomedical model.

00:08:18.557 --> 00:08:20.390 align:middle line:84%
If you didn't know, for
example, meditation.

00:08:20.390 --> 00:08:24.350 align:middle line:84%
If you went online to the
PubMed biomedical system, which

00:08:24.350 --> 00:08:28.100 align:middle line:84%
has 29 scientific publications,
there's over 5,000 studies

00:08:28.100 --> 00:08:31.940 align:middle line:84%
now on meditation,
about 4,500 on yoga,

00:08:31.940 --> 00:08:33.860 align:middle line:90%
probably 15,000 acupuncture.

00:08:33.860 --> 00:08:37.490 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of evidence how
these things are good for us,

00:08:37.490 --> 00:08:40.159 align:middle line:84%
and they help us reduce risk
factors and improve mood

00:08:40.159 --> 00:08:41.725 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:08:41.725 --> 00:08:43.100 align:middle line:84%
So those are the
ones that end up

00:08:43.100 --> 00:08:44.990 align:middle line:84%
in the biomedical
allopathic model

00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:46.590 align:middle line:90%
because the evidence is there.

00:08:46.590 --> 00:08:47.390 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:08:47.390 --> 00:08:49.580 align:middle line:84%
So it's really important
that the evidence is there.

00:08:49.580 --> 00:08:54.020 align:middle line:84%
Do you see any
preponderance of evidence

00:08:54.020 --> 00:08:56.630 align:middle line:84%
in fields that are just
being completely ignored

00:08:56.630 --> 00:08:59.052 align:middle line:90%
by the current paradigm?

00:08:59.052 --> 00:09:01.010 align:middle line:84%
>> The answer is yes,
and there's a fair amount

00:09:01.010 --> 00:09:05.390 align:middle line:84%
of evidence in the healing
touch, hands on healing model,

00:09:05.390 --> 00:09:09.050 align:middle line:84%
which is often called
biofield sciences these days.

00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:11.420 align:middle line:84%
But even though there's a
fair amount of evidence,

00:09:11.420 --> 00:09:12.660 align:middle line:90%
there still is resistance.

00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And I can understand why
because the western model

00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:18.290 align:middle line:90%
is very reductionistic.

00:09:18.290 --> 00:09:20.390 align:middle line:90%
You have to have evidence.

00:09:20.390 --> 00:09:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And right now there's
no scientific evidence

00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:26.600 align:middle line:84%
proving the existence of the
biofield, this field of energy

00:09:26.600 --> 00:09:28.610 align:middle line:90%
that surrounds a human being.

00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:30.230 align:middle line:84%
And we really need
that evidence.

00:09:30.230 --> 00:09:32.210 align:middle line:84%
And we have friends
who are working hard

00:09:32.210 --> 00:09:36.890 align:middle line:84%
to develop technologies that
can visualize it and show

00:09:36.890 --> 00:09:38.210 align:middle line:90%
the information in the field.

00:09:38.210 --> 00:09:40.960 align:middle line:84%
Once that's there
and developed, it's

00:09:40.960 --> 00:09:43.680 align:middle line:84%
